         <abstract>
            <p>To be useful for extremely stiff systems of ordinary differential equations, $A$-stability and a maximally damped condition as $\lambda h \rightarrow - \infty$ (i.e., $L$-stability) are desirable. This paper investigates the condition of $L$-stability for a class of Runge-Kutta methods known as the Rosenbrock procedure. This procedure requires only one computation of a Jacobian matrix per step of integration. $L$-stable Rosenbrock methods up to order four are derived.</p>
